cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the use of generative models for novelty detection in abnormal event and situational change detection from data series. This involves machine learning techniques such as one-class classifiers and unsupervised/semi-supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with anomaly and outlier detection, sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) may also be relevant.
